    "# 🧾 IBM Customer Churn Prediction — Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📌 Project Overview\n",
    "This project focuses on predicting customer churn for IBM Telecom using multiple machine learning models. The dataset is imbalanced, with:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **73.5%** Non-Churn (Class 0)\n",
    "- **26.5%** Churn (Class 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "Due to this imbalance, **accuracy is not a reliable metric**. Instead, the evaluation focused on:\n",
    "- ROC-AUC\n",
    "- Precision-Recall Curve\n",
    "- Churn Recall (Sensitivity)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📊 Dataset Summary\n",
    "- **Total Test Samples:** 1409  \n",
    "- **Class 0 (Not Churn):** 1035  \n",
    "- **Class 1 (Churn):** 374  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🤖 Models Evaluated\n",
    "The following models were trained and compared:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Logistic Regression (Tuned)\n",
    "- Random Forest (Tuned)\n",
    "- XGBoost (Tuned & Untuned)\n",
    "- Gradient Boosting (Tuned)\n",
    "- Artificial Neural Network (ANN)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🏆 Best Model Performance\n",
    "- **XGBoost (Tuned)** achieved the highest ROC-AUC (**0.843**), making it the best overall model.\n",
    "- **Logistic Regression (Tuned)** achieved the highest recall (**79%**), making it most effective at identifying churn customers.\n",
    "- **XGBoost (Untuned)** resulted in the lowest false negatives, which is critical in minimizing missed churn cases.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🔍 Key Insights\n",
    "- There is a **trade-off between recall and false negatives**:\n",
    "  - Higher recall → fewer missed churn customers\n",
    "  - Lower false negatives → better business retention strategy\n",
    "- Ensemble models (XGBoost, Gradient Boosting) performed best overall.\n",
    "- Random Forest showed weaker recall, making it less suitable for churn detection.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 💼 Business Impact\n",
    "- **False Negatives are costly** → customers leave without intervention.\n",
    "- A model with higher recall (like Logistic Regression) helps identify more at-risk customers.\n",
    "- A balanced model (like Tuned XGBoost) ensures both strong prediction power and business usability.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🏁 Final Recommendation\n",
    "- ✅ Use **XGBoost (Tuned)** for overall performance and stability  \n",
    "- ✅ Use **Logistic Regression** if the priority is maximizing churn detection  \n",
    "- ⚠️ Avoid relying solely on accuracy in imbalanced datasets  "
   ]
